Description: For sale is Rare sea foam green American made Peavey Reactor AX Telecaster. This really is a great playing and great sounding guitar. Will ship in a guitar bag with heavy padding within a shipping box for safe shipping. These have become quite collectible, with the Reactor AX being a preferred model in terms of quality build and amazing tone. I actually spent my early 20s collecting reactors as I thought they were a hidden gem that I preferred to fender telecasters but I have been slowly getting rid of them over the years as I never play anymore. This is the last to go. Regrettably as it took me forever to find one. Product Specs (per Peavey): U.S. made in Meridian, Mississippi, the Reactor AX is a single cutaway, "T-style" alder body electric guitar sporting 2 "Db2-T" dual blade humbucker pickups (designed by, and made in-house at, Peavey), a bolt-on neck, a 22-fret rosewood fingerboard with dot inlays, strings-through fixed bridge, six-on-one-side tuners, pearloid pickguard. Features: 25.5" Scale Length 12" Fretboard Radius 10 degree Reverse Headstock 22 Nickel Silver Frets Ash Body Rock Maple Neck, Rosewood fretboard Dual Blade Pickups String Through Body Tele Bridge Graphlon Nut 1 Master Volume & 1 Master Tone Control 3 way Selectore Switch Chrome Hardware
Title: Peavey Reactor AX vintage 90’s Sea foam
